    "severity": "HIGH",
    "category": "security",
    "location": "scripts/ai_agent_bridge/_cli.py:764",
    "description": "The proxy is described as localhost-only, but the CLI accepts any --host value and passes it directly to uvicorn with no guard and no authentication. If a user runs `ab serve --openai --host 0.0.0.0`, the service exposes an unauthenticated endpoint that launches local agent CLIs with the caller-provided prompt, which can consume paid quotas, access local agent configuration, and potentially expose local command outputs to the network. Reject non-loopback hosts unless an explicit unsafe flag and authentication mechanism are added."
  },
  {
    "id": "unbounded-request-body-to-subprocess",
    "severity": "MEDIUM",
    "category": "dos-surface",
    "location": "scripts/ai_agent_bridge/openai_proxy.py:31",
    "description": "The request model accepts unbounded message counts and unbounded string/list content, then flattens the whole body and sends it to subprocess-backed CLIs while capturing stdout/stderr in memory. A local or accidentally exposed client can submit very large payloads that drive high memory use, expensive model invocations, long subprocess lifetimes, or argument-size failures. Add explicit body/message/content limits at the HTTP boundary and reject over-limit requests with a 4xx response before spawning any backend."
  },
  {
    "id": "prompt-passed-via-argv",
    "severity": "MEDIUM",
    "category": "correctness",
    "location": "scripts/ai_agent_bridge/openai_proxy.py:177",
    "description": "The Gemini, Claude, and Hermes backends pass the entire user prompt as a command-line argument (`--prompt=...`, positional prompt, or `--oneshot=...`). Large but otherwise valid chat prompts can exceed the platform ARG_MAX limit and fail before reaching the model, and command-line arguments may also be visible through process listings while the backend is running. Prefer stdin or a temporary prompt file for all backends, as the Codex path already does."
  },
  {
    "id": "unsupported-openai-fields-silently-ignored",
    "severity": "MEDIUM",
    "category": "spec-compliance",
    "location": "scripts/ai_agent_bridge/openai_proxy.py:35",
    "description": "The request schema allows arbitrary extra OpenAI fields, but the endpoint silently ignores compatibility-sensitive options such as `stream`, `tools`, `tool_choice`, response formats, and sampling parameters. For example, an OpenAI client sending `stream: true` will expect an SSE stream but will receive a normal JSON completion, which can hang or break client integrations. Unsupported fields should either be implemented or explicitly rejected with a clear 400 error, especially for `stream` and tool-use envelopes."
  }
]

